oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Feedlot Nutrition
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: McCann, Chester
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: weaning calf
nutrition
feedlot cattle
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: It is certainly a pleasure to have an opportunity to visit with you gentlemen this afternoon concerning the area of feedlot nutrition. We will take a look at the various routes which the weaning calf might follow in reaching the position of a beef carcass with particular emphasis on the general aspects of nutrition in feedlot cattle.
